HEADWORD: Tripudiary
<hw>Tri*pu"di*a*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>tripudium</ets> a measured stamping, a leaping, a solemn religious
dance.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to dancing; performed by
dancing.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧ <xex>Tripudiary</xex>
augurations.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
